Subject: RE: [T2] Sealing exhaust leaks

Jason,

For the small leaks, I use a high temperature header silicone on both sides
of the gasket. It is orange in color and works very well.

Also, to get the flanges true, you have to take a hand rasp/file to them and
use a Sharpie to see the high points. A grinder's wheel tends to "dish" the
metal a little. Good for getting it close but a heavy rasp file will get you
closest.

I did this on my '78 exhaust system. A lot of elbow grease involved. With
the layer of silicone, no leaks in several thousand miles...

Jon Stiles
'68 Double Cab
'78 Westfalia

